<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-2-chapter-4-1%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
</article> 
<ol class="children">
<li class="comment byuser comment-author-mrvoid odd alt depth-2" id="li-comment-500075">
<article id="comment-500075" class="comment-body">
<footer class="comment-meta">
<div class="comment-author vcard"><img src="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/10/Salt-copy5.png" width="50" height="45" alt="MrVoid" class="avatar avatar-50 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-50 alignnone photo"/><span class="fn"><b>MrVoid</b> <br/><a href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/ti-index/ti-vol-2-chapter-4-1/#comment-500075"><time datetime="2016-11-14T12:56:16+00:00"> November 14, 2016 at 12:56 pm</time></a></span></div> </footer> 
<div class="comment-content">
<p>I blame Xuan.<br/>
I don&#8217;t think the story became boring, but his presence certainly did inflate the info dumps and amount of technical diarrhea in the narrative. Right now it&#8217;s seemingly at the tipping end of &#8220;too much for its own good&#8221;.</p>
<p>Also, I think the &#8220;game elements&#8221; are just there for flavor. The true meat is the Terror in Terror Infinity. The idea of tension and creeping danger. Which is what we&#8217;re currently lacking, seeing as they bickered among each other for a few good chapters now, and the whole flirting scenes with Lan and Zhang also came across in poor taste.<br/>
I don&#8217;t see why future arcs, or even this current arc, won&#8217;t be better. I just hope Xuan will learn to pipe it down a bit, and let the story develop naturally, rather than go every few sentences: &#8220;Woh, hold down there, let me tell you what we should do before you even speak.&#8221;<br/>
Solving everything like an unlikely OP-MC in xianxia, is just as bad as stopping every 2 seconds to overthink everything to perfection. Xuan is tipping too much towards the latter, or at least that&#8217;s how it comes across.</p>
</div> 
<div class="reply">
<a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-login" href="http://www.wuxiaworld.com/wp-login.php?redirect_to=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.wuxiaworld.com%2Fti-index%2Fti-vol-2-chapter-4-1%2F">Log in to Reply</a> <span>&darr;</span> </div> 
</article> 
</li> 
</ol> 
</li> 
</ol> 
